# Mini Browser App

Save this as `index.html` and open it in a browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Mini Browser</title>

  <style>
    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #111;
      color: white;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .topbar {
      display: flex;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 12px;
      background: #1e1e1e;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
    }

    input {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 12px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 10px;
      font-size: 16px;
      outline: none;
    }

    button {
      padding: 12px 18px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-weight: bold;
      background: #4caf50;
      color: white;
    }

    button:hover {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }

    .message {
      background: #222;
      padding: 8px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 14px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
    }

    iframe {
      width: 100%;
      height: calc(100vh - 102px);
      border: none;
      background: white;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="topbar">
    <input
      type="text"
      id="urlBox"
      placeholder="Enter website URL"
    />

    <button onclick="goToSite()">
      Go
    </button>
  </div>

  <div class="message">
    Some websites block iframe viewing for security reasons.
  </div>

  <iframe id="browserFrame"></iframe>

  <script>
    function goToSite() {
      let url = document.getElementById('urlBox').value.trim();

      if (!url) {
        alert('Enter a website URL');
        return;
      }

      if (!url.startsWith('http://') && !url.startsWith('https://')) {
        url = 'https://' + url;
      }

      document.getElementById('browserFrame').src = url;
    }

    document.getElementById('urlBox').addEventListener('keypress', function(e) {
      if (e.key === 'Enter') {
        goToSite();
      }
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
```

## How to Run

1. Open:

   * VS Code
2. Create a file named:

```txt
index.html
```

3. Paste the code.
4. Save the file.
5. Double-click the file OR use Live Server.

## Test Websites

Try:

```txt
example.com
```

Some large sites like Google or Discord block iframe embedding and will not display.
